    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait rly? \"textbook example of a success\"? i feel like people argue that it was a disaster because it basically turned the whole region into a vacuum for extremists and failed to account for the long-term consequences. aren't the geopolitical consequences just as important as the initial goal of removing Gaddafi?",
